<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,668,2043]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,774,801]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Description</emphasis>
. A small species, all specimens incomplete. 
<typeStatus box="[826,930,775,801]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[936,1021,775,802]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="6.8">6.8 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1089,1187,775,802]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="0.67">0.67 mm</quantity>
across thorax, with 37 setigers; large 
<typeStatus box="[314,410,811,837]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">paratype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[418,504,810,837]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[575,675,811,837]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.7" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="0.87">0.87 mm</quantity>
wide across thorax, with 30 setigers. Bodies relatively thick, robust in thoracic region with smooth crowded segments, each about four times wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[1155,1245,846,872]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1956,1981]" captionTargetBox="[180,1417,315,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[170,1417,308,1931]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leitoscoloplos sahlingi n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153567): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 1563568): B, anterior end, left lateral view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, middle abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634284/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
); abdominal segments becoming narrower and shorter. Dorsum of thorax rounded dorsally, venter flattened mid-ventrally; abdominal region flattened dorsally, rounded ventrally. Thoracic segments all uniannulate; abdominal segments becoming biannulate due to parapodial ridge elevated above rest of segment. Color in alcohol: light tan.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,668,2043]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Pre-setiger region about as long as first two setigers. Prostomium triangular, narrowing to pointed apex (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1956,1981]" captionTargetBox="[180,1417,315,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[170,1417,308,1931]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leitoscoloplos sahlingi n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153567): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 1563568): B, anterior end, left lateral view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, middle abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634284/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A–B); eyespots absent; nuchal organs prominent oval grooves on border with peristomium (
<figureCitation box="[1186,1274,1023,1050]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1956,1981]" captionTargetBox="[180,1417,315,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[170,1417,308,1931]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leitoscoloplos sahlingi n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153567): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 1563568): B, anterior end, left lateral view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, middle abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634284/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Peristomium composed of one achaetous ring extending ventrally, surrounding mouth (
<figureCitation box="[1006,1076,1059,1085]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1956,1981]" captionTargetBox="[180,1417,315,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[170,1417,308,1931]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leitoscoloplos sahlingi n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153567): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 1563568): B, anterior end, left lateral view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, middle abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634284/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A–B). Thorax with 12 setigers, abruptly separated from abdominal segments by loss of most neurosetae and increased size and shape of neuropodial lobe on setiger 13 (
<figureCitation box="[415,505,1130,1156]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1956,1981]" captionTargetBox="[180,1417,315,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[170,1417,308,1931]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leitoscoloplos sahlingi n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153567): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 1563568): B, anterior end, left lateral view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, middle abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634284/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,668,2043]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Thoracic notopodial and neuropodial lamellae elongate, digitiform, arising from broad base (
<figureCitation box="[1272,1363,1165,1191]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1956,1981]" captionTargetBox="[180,1417,315,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[170,1417,308,1931]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leitoscoloplos sahlingi n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153567): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 1563568): B, anterior end, left lateral view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, middle abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634284/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
), both similar in form; abdominal notopodia of anterior abdominal segments becoming long and narrow (
<figureCitation box="[1280,1372,1201,1227]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1956,1981]" captionTargetBox="[180,1417,315,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[170,1417,308,1931]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leitoscoloplos sahlingi n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153567): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 1563568): B, anterior end, left lateral view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, middle abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634284/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
). Abdominal neuropodia thickened, divided into a rounded terminal lobe and short laterally directed ventral cirrus (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1956,1981]" captionTargetBox="[180,1417,315,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[170,1417,308,1931]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leitoscoloplos sahlingi n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153567): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 1563568): B, anterior end, left lateral view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, middle abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634284/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
). Branchiae first present from setiger 10 (
<figureCitation box="[671,763,1272,1298]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1956,1981]" captionTargetBox="[180,1417,315,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[170,1417,308,1931]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leitoscoloplos sahlingi n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153567): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 1563568): B, anterior end, left lateral view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, middle abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634284/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
), short at first then increasing in size; branchiae of middle abdominal segments long, triangular, and flattened, tapering to narrow papilla (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1133,1307,1334]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1956,1981]" captionTargetBox="[180,1417,315,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[170,1417,308,1931]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leitoscoloplos sahlingi n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153567): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 1563568): B, anterior end, left lateral view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, middle abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634284/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
), each branchia about onethird longer than notopodial lamellae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,668,2043]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">All setae camerated capillaries except neuropodial aciculae; furcate and flail setae absent. Thoracic noto- and neurosetae with numerous capillaries organized in separate rows: 2–4 rows of notosetae and 4–5 rows of neurosetae. Abdominal notosetae include 7–8 capillaries, some long; abdominal neurosetae include 4–5 capillaries and 1–2 short protruding pointed aciculae, these minute.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,668,2043]" box="[199,467,1520,1546]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Pygidium not observed.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,668,2043]" box="[199,1340,1554,1582]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,431,1554,1582]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Methyl Green stain</emphasis>
. No pattern, prostomium not staining, body staining uniformly, de-stains rapidly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,668,2043]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
