<bibRefCitation author="Blake, J. A." box="[585,720,1626,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 145" refId="ref35753" refString="Blake, J. A. (2017) Polychaeta Orbiniidae from Antarctica, the Southern Ocean, the abyssal Pacific Ocean, and off South Amer- ica. Zootaxa, 4218 (1), 1 - 145. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4218.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Blake 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Four other species in this category occur in the eastern Pacific: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fauchald" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[151,299,1663,1688]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[151,299,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
