<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,152,287]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,153,179]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etymology</emphasis>
. This species is named for the late Dr. Heiko Sahling (
<date box="[932,1064,152,179]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1969" valueMax="2018">1969–2018</date>
), marine ecologist, who collected and provided these specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Day" authorityYear="1977" box="[538,701,188,214]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[538,701,188,214]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Leitoscoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other polychaetes from the Cascadia Subduction Zone and authored an important paper on the macrofauna of the site (
<bibRefCitation author="Sahling, H. &amp; Rickert, D. &amp; Lee, R. W. &amp; Linke, P. &amp; Suess, E." box="[815,1033,224,251]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="121 - 138" refId="ref39107" refString="Sahling, H., Rickert, D., Lee, R. W., Linke, P. &amp; Suess, E. (2002) Macrofaunal community structure and sulfide flux at gas hydrate deposits from the Cascadia convergent margin, NE Pacific. Marine Ecology Progress Series, 231, 121 - 138. https: // doi. org / 10.3354 / meps 231121" type="journal article" year="2002">
Sahling 
<emphasis box="[909,958,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
